quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  23,23,"(We took care of your physical and mental needs.) And, indeed, We sent (Our first Prophet), Noah to his people and he said, \"O My people! Serve Allah. You have no god other than Him. Will you not then be mindful of Him and walk aright"
  23,24,"But the leaders among his community who refused to acknowledge the Truth, said, \"This is only a man like you who wants to become prominent among you. God could have sent angels if He willed (to convey a message to us). We never heard this from our forefathers"
  23,25,"He is nothing but a madman, so watch him for a while"
  23,26,"Said he, \"My Lord! Help me, for they accuse me of lying"
  23,27,"Then We revealed unto him thus, \"Build, under Our eyes and according to Our revealed instructions, the ark. Then, as Our Command comes to pass and the torrent gushes forth, take on board a couple each of the domesticated animals. As well as your family and followers except him against whom the Word has already gone forth (for his persistent denial). And do not plead with Me on behalf of the oppressors. Verily, they will be drowned"
  23,28,"When you have settled in the ship along with your companions, say, \"All Praise is due to Allah Who has saved us from the oppressors"
  23,29,"And say, \"O My Sustainer! Enable me to disembark with Your blessing. You are the Best Director of destinations"
  23,30,"Behold, herein are Messages indeed, for Our Law keeps testing nations (for viability)"
  23,31,(And after those people of old) We gave rise to new generations
  23,32,"And always We sent to them a Messenger of their own. (Without exception each of these Messengers said), \"Serve Allah. You have no god other than Him. Will you not then be mindful of Him and walk aright"